 8:27
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='496303' id='t-496303'>So what did we discover?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='498958' id='t-498958'>Well one of the unique texts in Archimedes</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='501140' id='t-501140'>is called &quot;The Stomachion.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='502943' id='t-502943'>And this didn't exist in Codices A and B.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='505357' id='t-505357'>And we knew that it involved this square.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='507776' id='t-507776'>And this is a perfect square,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='509569' id='t-509569'>and it's divided into 14 bits.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='511590' id='t-511590'>But no one knew what Archimedes was doing with these 14 bits.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='514373' id='t-514373'>And now we think we know.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='516557' id='t-516557'>He was trying to work out</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='518324' id='t-518324'>how many ways you can recombine those 14 bits</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='520857' id='t-520857'>and still make a perfect square.</span>
