<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
10:50
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='639514' id='t-639514'>Now I should say at this point</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='641163' id='t-641163'>that normally when you're looking</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='643930' id='t-643930'>at medieval manuscripts that have been scraped off,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='645926' id='t-645926'>you don't find unique texts.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='647412' id='t-647412'>And to find two in one manuscript is really something.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='650514' id='t-650514'>To find three is completely weird.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='653731' id='t-653731'>And we found three.</span>
